Start
/ Reading %!error.callback% outside an error handler scope: %!error% itself is
/ null (no AsyncLocal-flowed error in this context), so the callback path is
/ unresolved. Coder flipped the default from "throws" to "null" — simpler
/ runtime contract, matches how %!error.X% works generally outside scope.
- set %callbackOutsideScope% = %!error.callback%
- assert %callbackOutsideScope% is null
